            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/grandparentdetail"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:visibility="gone"
                android:text="Once the primary applicant cleared the minimum residence time there to sponsor any other individual PR, then he/she can call on their parents or grandparents to Canada. So if you also want to sponsor your parents or grandparents, then make sure that you have checked the below-listed eligibility criteria once.
Applicant must be at least 18 years old and live in Canada as a Canadian resident or permanent resident of Canada.
He/she must have enough money to support parents/ grandparents in Canada. For that, the government requires proof of income.
However, there are certain circumstances, when the government of Canada will not allow an individual to sponsor parents/grandparents like:
\n\u25CF When an individual is in jail or penalized
\n\u25CF When an individual didnâ€™t pay back or missed the loan, bond or court-ordered family support in the past.
\n\u25CF When an individual is declared bankrupt."
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:layout_marginLeft="16dp"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:layout_marginRight="5dp"
                android:paddingLeft="16dp"
                android:textColor="@color/black"
                app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent"
                app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
                app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf="@+id/eligibilitygpLayout" />


